#### **Part 3: Data Engineering Architecture**

**3.1 Institutional Datasets (Select One)**

| Dataset | Scale & Key Columns |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Indian Stock Market Minute-Level** | 720M+ rows. `symbol`, `timestamp`, `open, high, low, close`, `volume`, `oi`. |
| **FNSPID (News + S&P 500)** | 29.7M prices + 15.7M news records. `Date`, `Ticker`, `Open, High, Low, Close, Volume`, plus text headlines. |
| **Optiver Realized Volatility** | 167M rows of order book data. `stock_id`, `time_id`, `seconds_in_bucket`, `bid/ask` prices/sizes. |
| **S&P 500 Daily Stocks** | Daily historical data for all components. `Date`, `Symbol`, `Open, High, Low, Close, Adj Close`, `Volume`. |

**3.2 Data Pipeline Requirements**

- **Survivorship Bias Mitigation:** Reconstruct the active asset universe at each historical rebalancing date using point-in-time constituent lists.
- **Time-Series Alignment:** Use a canonical calendar with outer joins. Forward-fill missing values using the last valid price.
- **Corporate Action Adjustments:** Calculate split-adjusted log returns:
  
  $$r_{i,t} = \ln\left(\frac{P^{\text{adj}}_{i,t}}{P^{\text{adj}}_{i,t-1}}\right)$$

- **High-Frequency Aggregation (for minute-level data):** Resample to 15-minute/hourly bars using Volume-Weighted Average Price (VWAP):
  
  $$\text{VWAP}_{i,T} = \frac{\sum_{k \in T} P_{i,k} \times V_{i,k}}{\sum_{k \in T} V_{i,k}}$$

